With the assumption that phenotype similarity between two diseases can be explained by genotype similarity between them, known as the “guilt by association” principle [63], Glints extends our previous work [55, 64] and simultaneously regresses three types of phenotype similarities derived from HPO, MeSH and UMLS by each of the nine functional similarities between genes. In detail, given two diseases indexed by d and e, we present their phenotype similarities as y
